                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The First Committee of the United Nations General Assembly met on the afternoon
                    of December 7 from 3 to 4:15 p. m.; for the record, see U.K document
                    A/C.1/SR.409. At this meeting, the Committee by a vote of 42 to 5, with 4
                    abstentions, agreed to give priority to debating the question of intervention by
                    the Central People’s Government of the People’s Republic of China in Korea. The
                    First Committee, however, did not vote during the remainder of its sessions
                    during 1950 on the six-power draft resolution (see the editorial note, <ref
                        target="#pg_1421">page 1421</ref>).</p>
            </div>
